                    <state type="martyr" source="#bib1296-2">
                        <p>Martyr</p>
                    </state>
                    <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bib1296-2">AMS, II, 539- 58 ; BHO, 394.
Lagrange, 156-68 ; Leclercq, III, 333- 43.
Suhadii', II, 300- 15.
P. Devos, "Le dossier hagiographique de saint Jacques l'Intercis", AB 71 (1953),
157- 78.
Autres Actes orientaux : BHO, 395- 98.
Fiey, "Hagiographie" , 455.
BS, VI, 356- 62 (J.-M. SaugetfM. Chiara Celletti).</quote>
                    </note>
                    <note type="abstract" xml:id="abstract-en-1296">Jacob "the cut-up" was a noble Persian from
          the Royal City of <placeName ref=" http://syriaca.org/place/35">Beth Lapaṭ</placeName>. He
          became a Christian, but he later abjured his Christian identity. His family reproached
          him, so he confessed his faith before Bahram V and was martyred.</note>
